        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 2:52PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 250 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with frequent
lightning along a line extending from 15 miles south of
Hendersonville to 4 miles southwest of Easley to 8 miles north of
Hartwell, and moving southeast at 20 mph.

Locations to be impacted include...
Greenville Downtown, Anderson, Easley, Greenville Eastside, West
Greenville, Berea, Welcome, Homeland Park, Powdersville, and
Piedmont.

In addition to intense lightning, very heavy rainfall rates up to 2
inches per hour and wind gusts to 40 mph will be possible in these
areas.
</description>
